  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Remove 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]<strong> </span>butter</strong> from the fridge to warm up for later</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into <strong>chips </strong>and add to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt, </strong>then put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until the chips are golden and starting to crisp – these are your <strong>smoky chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686667705529-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686667705529-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686667705529-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686667705529-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686667705529-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut a piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A4 sheet of paper</p><p>Lay 1 <strong>garlic clove </strong>per person (skin on) in the middle of the foil, then add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, a small splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686667708406-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686667708406-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686667708406-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686667708406-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686667708406-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Scrunch the edges of the tin foil together around the garlic to form a sealed parcel</p><p>Add the <strong>garlic parcel</strong> to a separate tray and put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the garlic is soft</p><p>Once soft, carefully remove the skin from the <strong>roasted garlic</strong>,<strong> </strong>mash with a fork and set aside – this is your <strong>mashed roasted garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686667712284-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686667712284-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686667712284-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686667712284-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686667712284-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the garlic is roasting, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the<strong> chopped parsley</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in a small bowl with the <strong>warmed butter </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>cheesy garlic butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1686667716655-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
